BREAST-COMPOSITION: fibro fatty and glandular breast parenchyma (ACR C)
FINDINGS: A few well-defined soft opacities seen in the posterior part of the upper quadrant of the breast suggest probably benign lesions (BIRADS 3). No abnormal microcalcifications are observed. The skin, nipple, and pectoral muscle appear normal. No significant axillary adenopathy is noted.
